  "What does 'actual cash value' (ACV) mean in insurance?": "",
  "The maximum amount an insurance policy will pay": "",
  "The amount of cash in your bank account": "",
  "The replacement cost of an item minus depreciation, reflecting what the item was worth at the time of loss": "",
  "ACV = replacement cost minus depreciation. A 5-year-old laptop that costs $1,200 new might have an ACV of $400. ACV policies pay less than replacement cost policies.": "",
  "What is an 'insurance rider' or 'endorsement'?": "",
