  "$9,000 — the entire withdrawal is tax savings": "",
  "$996 — only the contribution deduction": "",
  "Contribution deduction: $4,150 x 0.24 = $996. Tax-free growth on $4,850 gain: $4,850 x 0.24 = $1,164. Total savings = $996 + $1,164 = $2,160. The triple tax advantage compounds over time.": "",
  "A homeowner in a flood zone pays $1,200/year for flood insurance. Their home is worth $300,000 and the annual probability of a significant flood is 2%. Is this insurance cost-effective based on expected value?": "",
